        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-11-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-11-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="376"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d376">
                <head>376. Telegram 1272 to Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d376fn1">Source:
                        Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/11–1655. Official Use Only.
                        Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_CRN_1">Clough</persName>; cleared by
                            <persName corresp="#p_LJMH_1">Lindbeck</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_RWS_1">Robertson</persName>, and Sebald.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1955-11-17">November 17, 1955, 7:49 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d376-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d376-1"/>
                <p>1272. For <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>. Your 1186.</p>
                <p>AP Tokyo reports Peiping broadcast November 17 announcing release Mrs. Bradshaw,
                    White and Garvey. No confirmation yet but presume will be confirmed due course.
                    View this news believe inadvisable use text article your 1186 Ford column
                    Friday. It would require extensive revision and would be considerably weakened
                    well as overshadowed by news of release three Americans.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HH_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Hoover</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
